<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Hays Code's impact on Hollywood films in the 1920s and 1930s:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Promoted artistic freedom</option>
            <option letter="b">Established strict moral guidelines for content</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased political commentary</option>
            <option letter="d">Encouraged controversial themes</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Hays Code, developed in the 1920s and strictly enforced starting in 1934, established rigid moral guidelines for film content. Named after Will Hays, it prohibited or restricted depictions of various behaviors and themes deemed morally objectionable, including violence, sexual content, and challenges to authority. This self-imposed censorship system significantly shaped Hollywood film content for several decades.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
